 "Title":"Requires any website or mobile application associated with an electronic benefit transfer system to be offered in the twelve most common non-English languages",
 "Summary":"Requires any website or mobile application associated with an electronic benefit transfer system to be offered in the twelve most common non-English languages spoken by limited-English proficient individuals in the state, based on data in the most recent American Community Survey published by the United States Census Bureau.",
 "LawSection":"Social Services Law","LawCode":"Amd §21-a, Soc Serv L",
